data.name: infoRichTextBoxLeft.ToolTip
data.value: A tag in bold indicates it is not on the other file. A tag in italics indicates it is found in your custom tag library. A tag in both bold & italics indicates both of the above things. 'Tags' is in quotes as this program can only guess what is intended as a tag and what is not.

data.name: infoRichTextBoxRight.ToolTip

data.name: onlyKeepLibraryTagsCheckBox.ToolTip
data.value: When using the "Merge File Tags" option, if this option is ticked then only tags that are found within your custom tag collection will be kept in the merge. This can be useful to get rid of "non-tags" like post IDs, eg. 127437018616.
